<T>__{dissolve:}
<L>__{exterior radio city night (stock)}
<A>__{it is raining. the lights are on in the buildings.}
<L>__{interior jim's office night}
<A>__{mary is attending to some detail work as the door opens and jim enters, disturbed. mary looks at him questioningly.}
<C>__{jim}
<D>__{you'd better send out for coffee and sandwiches,... it looks like an all night session.}
<C>__{mary}
<P>__{(concerned)}
<D>__{what did he say?}
<C>__{jim}
<P>__{(wearily, seating himself at desk)}
<D>__{tomorrow morning.}
<C>__{mary}
<P>__{(sighs)}
<D>__{well, i guess you'll just have to dream something up good or bad.}
<C>__{jim}
<D>__{i rather got the impression it had better be good.}
<C>__{mary}
<P>__{(raised eyebrow)}
<D>__{oh.}
<A>__{he picks up a pencil, nibbles on it thoughtfully. the silence in the room is broken only by the patter of raindrops on the window. it strikes a note in jim's subconscious. he swivels around in his chair and stares soberly out the window.}
<C>__{jim}
<P>__{(ruminatively, almost to himself)}
<D>__{funny how you look forward to the little things. rain, for instance.}
<A>__{mary looks at him curiously. he turns to her.}
<C>__{jim}
<D>__{for a month now, i guess i've been looking forward to the first rainy night at the house.}
<P>__{(looks at muriel's picture)}
<D>__{big blazing fire. muriel knitting. me in my new smoking jacket... with my pipe and slippers, reading my paper...}
<P>__{(sighs)}
<D>__{oh, well.}
<A>__{as he starts to work.}
